    "body": "Problem:\nThis fixes the same problem as #36519.  The same traceback from that other PR appears, but from line 351.\n\nSolution:\nI'm sorry, I don't understand enough about Neovim internals to understand under what circumstances `state.buffers[bufnr]` might be nil, but when it is, this code blows up, triggering a traceback on every keystroke.\n",
    "closed_at": "2026-06-16T20:20:17Z",
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This code gets called asynchronously so could be a race. And yes, we don't need to suffer while waiting for a more \"correct\" fix.\r\n\r\nIf another such case is found, then it's probably time to dig in and add some logging/asserts/etc to box in the root cause.",
            "created_at": "2026-06-16T20:19:43Z",
